      <h2>Understanding US Document Attestation</h2>
      
      <p>The United States presents unique challenges for document attestation due to its federal system. Unlike countries with centralized government document issuance, most US documents originate from state authorities rather than the federal government. This means your California degree, Texas birth certificate, or Florida marriage certificate each requires authentication from different state offices before federal authentication can proceed.</p>

